vchProductDescription: Karo Dark combines the natural sweetness of pure corn syrup with a small amount of refiner's syrup (a cane sugar product with a molasses-like flavor). Most famous as the ingredient in Pecan Pie. It is an easy-blendin, natural sweetener that enhances the flavor and texture of many foods, such as baked goods, caramel popcorn, candy, meat and vegetable glazes, fruit toppings and beverages. Karo Corn Syrup has a consistent viscosity providing proven performance for high quality products. Karo has been known for trusted quality since 1902.
vchAdditionalDescription: Karo has been known for trusted quality since 1902. Karo Blue Label Corn Syrup has a consistent viscosity and sweetness level essential for high quality products.
vchServingSuggestions: Karo Dark Corn Syrup is an essential ingredient for making delicious pecan pies, traditional candies, caramel corn, baked goods, sauces and glazes, and so much more. Gluten free. Contains no high fructose corn syrup.
vchPreparation: Corn syrup serves different functions in different types of recipes. It controls sugar crystallization in candy, prevents the formation of ice crystals in frozen desserts, enhances fresh fruit flavor in jams and preserves, sweetens and thickens relishes and chutneys. Corn syrup balances sweet and sour flavor profiles, and is therefore a key ingredient in many Asian dishes. When brushed onto baked ham, barbecued meats or baked vegetables corn syrup is an ideal glaze. In baked goods, corn syrup holds moisture and maintains freshness longer. Karo Light and Dark corn syrups perform similarly in recipes and can usually be used interchangeably. Typically, Karo Dark Corn Syrup is used when a more robust molasses-like flavor is desired whereas Karo Light Corn Syrup is used when a more delicate flavor is desired. Recipes usually specify which type to use but the choice may be guided by personal preference.
vchStorage: This product is packaged in a blue drum with a sealed lid. For best results, store tightly closed in an ambient temperature, not to exceed 100Â° F. Shelf life is 3 years.
vchIngredientStatement: Dark corn syrup, Refiners' syrup, caramel flavor, salt, sodium benzoate (used to protect quality),caramelcolor.

vchPreparation: Corn syrup serves different functions in different types of recipes. It controls sugar crystallization in candy, prevents the formation of ice crystals in frozen desserts, enhances fresh fruit flavor in jams and preserves, sweetens and thickens relishes and chutneys. Corn syrup balances sweet and sour flavor profiles, and is therefore a key ingredient in many Asian dishes. When brushed onto baked ham, barbecued meats or baked vegetables corn syrup is an ideal glaze. In baked goods, corn syrup holds moisture and maintains freshness longer. Karo Light and Dark corn syrups perform similarly in recipes and can usually be used interchangeably. Typically, Karo Dark Corn Syrup is used when a more robust molasses-like flavor is desired whereas Karo Light Corn Syrup is used when a more delicate flavor is desired. Recipes usually specify which type to use but the choice may be guided by personal preference.

vchProductDescription: Karo Light is pure corn syrup made with real vanilla. Most famous as the ingredient in Pecan Pie. It is an easy-blendin, natural sweetener that enhances the flavor and texture of many foods, such as baked goods, caramel popcorn, candy, meat and vegetable glazes, fruit toppings and beverages. Karo Corn Syrup has a consistent viscosity providing proven performance for high quality products. Karo has been known for trusted quality since 1902.
vchServingSuggestions: Karo Light Corn Syrup is an essential ingredient for making delicious pecan pies, traditional candies, caramel corn, baked goods, sauces and glazes, and so much more. Gluten free. Contains no high fructose corn syrup.
vchPreparation: Corn syrup serves different functions in different types of recipes. It controls sugar crystallization in candy, prevents the formation of ice crystals in frozen desserts, enhances fresh fruit flavor in jams and preserves, sweetens and thickens relishes and chutneys. Corn syrup balances sweet and sour flavor profiles, and is therefore a key ingredient in many Asian dishes. When brushed onto baked ham, barbecued meats or baked vegetables corn syrup is an ideal glaze. In baked goods, corn syrup holds moisture and maintains freshness longer. Karo Light and Dark corn syrups perform similarly in recipes and can usually be used interchangeably. Typically, Karo Dark Corn Syrup is used when a more robust molasses-like flavor is desired whereas Karo Light Corn Syrup is used when a more delicate flavor is desired. Recipes usually specify which type to use but the choice may be guided by personal preference.
vchStorage: This product is packaged in a white pail with pour spout and handle. For best results, store tightly closed in an ambient temperature, not to exceed 100Â° F. Shelf life is 3 years.
vchIngredientStatement: Corn syrup, salt, vanilla extract (vanilla beans, water, ethyl alcohol)

vchProductDescription: Karo Dark combines the natural sweetness of pure corn syrup with a small amount of refiner's syrup (a cane sugar product with a molasses-like flavor). Most famous as the ingredient in Pecan Pie. It is an easy-blendin, natural sweetener that enhances the flavor and texture of many foods, such as baked goods, caramel popcorn, candy, meat and vegetable glazes, fruit toppings and beverages. Karo Corn Syrup has a consistent viscosity providing proven performance for high quality products. Karo has been known for trusted quality since 1902.
vchAdditionalDescription: Karo has been known for trusted quality since 1902. Karo Blue Label Corn Syrup has a consistent viscosity and sweetness level essential for high quality products.
vchServingSuggestions: Karo Dark Corn Syrup is an essential ingredient for making delicious pecan pies, traditional candies, caramel corn, baked goods, sauces and glazes, and so much more. Gluten free. Contains no high fructose corn syrup.
vchPreparation: Corn syrup serves different functions in different types of recipes. It controls sugar crystallization in candy, prevents the formation of ice crystals in frozen desserts, enhances fresh fruit flavor in jams and preserves, sweetens and thickens relishes and chutneys. Corn syrup balances sweet and sour flavor profiles, and is therefore a key ingredient in many Asian dishes. When brushed onto baked ham, barbecued meats or baked vegetables corn syrup is an ideal glaze. In baked goods, corn syrup holds moisture and maintains freshness longer. Karo Light and Dark corn syrups perform similarly in recipes and can usually be used interchangeably. Typically, Karo Dark Corn Syrup is used when a more robust molasses-like flavor is desired whereas Karo Light Corn Syrup is used when a more delicate flavor is desired.  Recipes usually specify which type to use but the choice may be guided by personal preference.
vchStorage: This product is packaged in a white pail with pour spout and handle. For best results, store tightly closed in an ambient temperature, not to exceed 100Â° F. Shelf life is 3 years.
vchIngredientStatement: Corn Syrup, Refiners' Molasses, Natural Flavor, Salt, Sodium Benzoate (used to protect quality), Caramel Color.

vchProductDescription: Karo Light is pure corn syrup made with real vanilla. Most famous as the ingredient in Pecan Pie. It is an easy-blendin, natural sweetener that enhances the flavor and texture of many foods, such as baked goods, caramel popcorn, candy, meat and vegetable glazes, fruit toppings and beverages. Karo Corn Syrup has a consistent viscosity providing proven performance for high quality products. Karo has been known for trusted quality since 1902.
vchAdditionalDescription: Adding flavor to your dishes will increase consumption as well as ensure the maximum satisfaction from your customers.
vchServingSuggestions: Karo Light Corn Syrup is an essential ingredient for making delicious pecan pies, traditional candies, caramel corn, baked goods, sauces and glazes, and so much more. Gluten free.  Contains no high fructose corn syrup.
vchPreparation: Corn syrup serves different functions in different types of recipes. It controls sugar crystallization in candy, prevents the formation of ice crystals in frozen desserts, enhances fresh fruit flavor in jams and preserves, sweetens and thickens relishes and chutneys. Corn syrup balances sweet and sour flavor profiles, and is therefore a key ingredient in many Asian dishes. When brushed onto baked ham, barbecued meats or baked vegetables corn syrup is an ideal glaze. In baked goods, corn syrup holds moisture and maintains freshness longer. Karo Light and Dark corn syrups perform similarly in recipes and can usually be used interchangeably. Typically, Karo Dark Corn Syrup is used when a more robust molasses-like flavor is desired whereas Karo Light Corn Syrup is used when a more delicate flavor is desired. Recipes usually specify which type to use but the choice may be guided by personal preference.
vchStorage: This product is packaged in a blue drum with a sealed lid. For best results, store tightly closed in an ambient temperature, not to exceed 100Â° F. Shelf life is 3 years.
